-- Malaysia Police Confirm 3 Blasts, 2 Hurt Near Court After Anwar Not Guilty
-- B y   C h o n g   P o o i   K o o n
-- 2012-01-09T03:54:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-09/malaysia-police-confirm-3-blasts-2-hurt-near-court-after-anwar-not-guilty.html
Malaysian police confirmed three
explosions took place near the  Kuala Lumpur  court house today
where political opposition leader  Anwar Ibrahim  was earlier
acquitted of sodomy.  Two members of the public were injured in the incidents and
taken to hospital, city police said on their Facebook page.
Police are investigating, the statement said. Anwar had already
left the area, according to Bloomberg reporters at the scene.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chong Pooi Koon in Kuala Lumpur at 
